2) Array methods: Never call on a value that could be null/undefined/non-array. Guarded as:
   - (items ?? []).map(...) or Array.isArray(items) ? items.map(...) : []
3) React useState for arrays/objects: Initialize with correct type — useState<Type[]>([]) (no useState() or useState(null) for arrays)
4) API response shapes: Validate — const list = Array.isArray(response?.data) ? response.data : []
5) Optional chaining: Use obj?.property?.nested when accessing nested API results
